02/04/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) leader Cedomir Jovanovic said on Tuesday (April 1st) he hopes the Democratic Party (DS)-G17 Plus and the LDP will be in position to form a government after Serbia's early parliamentary elections on May 11th.
Jovanovic, a former DS whip, is one of the few political leaders in Serbia who publicly says Belgrade must recognise Kosovo's independence.
(Blic, Danas, Politika - 02/04/08;
RTS, Tanjug, Beta - 01/04/08)
